            <title>[SOLR-16214] Fix lunr-extension usage in ref-guide build</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16214</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We currently use the supplemental-ui option to include search functionality in the ref-guide, via the &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitlab.com/antora/antora-lunr-extension&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitlab.com/antora/antora-lunr-extension&lt;/a&gt; project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recently, they have improved the usage of this extension so that you don&apos;t have to use the supplemental-ui at all when building the site. The extension will automatically add all necessary ui-components for searching.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gitlab.com/antora/antora-lunr-extension/-/issues/15&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitlab.com/antora/antora-lunr-extension/-/issues/15&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
